channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: June 17, 2024 - Israel-Gaza news
item.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has disbanded the country's war cabinet, an Israeli official says, just over a week after opposition leader Benny Gantz withdrew from the body.

item.title: Southern New Mexico wildfire leads to evacuation of village of 7,000
item.description: Residents of the southern New Mexico Village of Ruidoso have been ordered to flee their homes without taking time to grab any belongings due to a fast-moving wildfire

item.title: Nvidia, Apple, and Microsoft Could Help This Stock-Split ETF Turn $200,000 Into $1 Million
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Iowa law letting authorities charge people facing deportation blocked for now
item.description: A federal judge temporarily blocked an Iowa law allowing law enforcement to file charges​ against people with outstanding deportation orders or who'd been denied entry to the U.S.

item.title: Confessions of a 1980s flight attendant
item.description: Ann Hood, a best-selling author, has recounted her adventures working as cabin crew on TWA flights in the 1980s in a book detailing the highs and lows of life during the early jet age.

item.title: Celtics win 18th NBA championship with 106-88 Game 5 victory over Dallas Mavericks
item.description: Jayson Tatum had 31 points, 11 assists and eight rebounds as the Celtics topped the Dallas Mavericks 106-88 to claim the franchise’s 18th championship, breaking a tie with the Los Angeles Lakers for the most in league history

item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Georgia father freed from prison 10 years after toddler died in hot car
item.description: Justin Ross Harris was freed on Father's Day from the Macon State Prison a decade after his 22-month-old son Cooper died, records show.

item.title: June 13, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: The US-backed Gaza ceasefire proposal doesn't meet Hamas' demands for an end to the war, a senior official has told CNN. Osama Hamdan also said that "no one has an idea" how many of the hostages held in the enclave are alive.

item.title: Judge grants request to share confidential docs in 2019 Boeing MAX crash with DOJ
item.description: A federal magistrate judge on Monday granted a request from families of victims of the 2019 Ethiopian Air Boeing 737 MAX crash to provide the DOJ confidential documents.

item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: In Virginia GOP primary, Trump, McCarthy try to oust House Freedom Caucus chair
item.description: House Freedom Caucus Chairman Bob Good is running for reelection, and both Trump and former House Speaker Kevin McCarthy are backing his primary opponent.

item.title: Biden and Zelensky lay out new US support for Ukraine
item.description: US President Joe Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signed a new security agreement Thursday as world leaders gathered for the G7 summit in Italy.

item.title: Biden to announce relief for some undocumented spouses of US citizens, 'Dreamers'
item.description: President Biden will announce two new executive actions that could provide relief to thousands of undocumented immigrants who have been in the country for several years.

item.title: US renews warning it's obligated to defend the Philippines after its new clash with China at sea
item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: New Mexico village orders all residents to evacuate due to raging wildfire
item.description: Residents of the village of Ruidoso in southern New Mexico were ordered to flee their homes Monday without even taking time to grab any belongings due to a fast-moving wildfire.

item.title: Supreme Court maintains access to abortion pill in unanimous decision
item.description: The Supreme Court has issued a decision on whether the US Food and Drug Administration overstepped its authority by expanding access to the abortion pill mifepristone.

item.title: Russian President Vladimir Putin to arrive in North Korea for state visit
item.description: Russia's President Vladimir Putin is expected to arrive in Pyongyang, North Korea, Tuesday evening.

item.title: Biden plan offers legal status to 500,000 immigrant spouses of U.S. citizens
item.description: The Biden administration's program will benefit unauthorized immigrants with American citizen spouses, if they have lived in the U.S. for at least 10 years.
